A decade in now, but THIS WAS NEVER MY GOAL!

Only because I never knew it was possible. My friends would say "you could design for Michigan Football". And I would laugh and respond, "If only there was an actual position like that".

My goal was to be a high school head coach, and I did coach for 10 seasons, but that was not my calling. 

 I was designing for fun and posting on social media as a hobby, when I got a call from the Dir. of PP (Shout to my guys @csing1 and Dan Ifft) at the University of Michigan. He asked me if I could come down to Ann Arbor for a meeting. I will never forget that feeling of pure elation. 

At the meeting, they asked if I could make a couple samples for them in the next week or two. I said, "No, but I will send you 2-3 designs EVERY day, as long as you use them". 

I would go to my full-time job for 40-60 hours a week, and then design until 2:00-3:00am every night for an additional 40 hours. 

A few months later a creative position opened up for the first time at U-M football and I accepted. It was far less money than I was making at the time, but my wife trusted me, I quit my job and we jumped in with both feet. We both bet on me!

A decade later and a lot has changed since then. There isn't anywhere in the world I would rather be. I can't imagine anything more rewarding. I am one of the lucky ones that "GETS TO" come into Schembechler Hall every day and proudly represent the block M on my chest. #GoBlue
